<br>
I am sure there are plenty of reasons a soft skin would do the quest if he could, but...<br>
<br>
No, Iksar would not give the relic out to an outsider. Let's look at their society and their religion.<br>
<br>
They kill, anyone of their own kind, for even suggesting not worshipping Cazic-Thule. If you aren't a Cazicite, then it's completely out of the question they'd ever even let you in their city, let alone give you their most sacred relic. By letting a NON Cazicite walk around their city, they are treating soft skins BETTER then they treat their own people, and are not just &quot;bending their rules&quot;, they are downright ignoring the very principle of their society. Somehow, I don't see Iksar doing that. <br>
<br>
Second, their society is caste based, you are born, bred, raised and taught certain things and certain things are assumed of you. You are assigned a specific profession and if you disagree with what you are assigned, your killed. Anyone who wasn't bred this way can't be trusted, soft skins might trust an outsider, but Iksar don't, they are not like that. Iksar are not soft skins. They don't allow anyone who doesn't swear complete loyalty to the Empire to stay within their ranks, again, letting soft skins in implies they treat outsiders better then their own people, and tolerate different beliefs, ways of life and non Imperial intrests when their entire society is centerd around NOT doing or tolerating that.<br>
<br>
Third, Greenmist is a sacred, holy relic of their people and culture. They are a xenophobic race of fanatics, but race is the indeed the highest determining thing in whether or not they like you. Iksar hate greed, they hate selfishness, they hate deciet, and they hate any who might have any of those qualities. Letting a soft skin, a non Cazicite, an outsider, and one who isn't loyal to the Empire wield their most sacred sword? I do not think so. As another said, the entire quest was written with the mind an Iksar would be doing it, not a soft skin. The weapon was originally Iksar only.<br>
<br>
This is almost completely and totally UnRPable from the Iksar side. Iksar wouldn't let soft skins in their city let alone give them their relics. I worked out a semi believable reason for this with the first soft skin I encounterd doing Greenmist, because he was willing to modify his roleplay story a bit to accomodate the Iksar. Verant even basically admidited to me this is UnRPable from the Iksar side and they simply do not care.<br>
<br>
Do I blame you for doing the quest? No. It's there, it's available, I have no right to blame you for doing it. Am I angry that it happens at all? Very. I am extremely angry at Verant for making the item soft skin usable. It's simply wrong. Espicially considering right after they changed the Iksar weapons to soft skin usable, they put in racial items for dark elves and halflings, and there is still a Tunare Paladin only alternate epic. I took it up with Verant, they do not care, at all.<br>
<br>
I have nothing against you personally Ooiioo, and I hope you have fun in EQ and continue to enjoy the game in your own way. But this sitution makes me extremely angry and RPing an Iksar is pretty much impossible if there are soft skins running around our city left and right picking up our sacred relics. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A> at: 6/24/02 9:25:35 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uoogmog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oogmog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/24/02 11:14:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2174.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Greenmist/Khukri Test of Pain</span><hr size=1> Well, I had a long written post of my stance on this subject, but to a point it just started sounding repetitive.  Ones idea of RP, could be completely different to anothers.  I for one feel if a NON iksar would go through the pains of obtaining all the pieces before TLC hit, and in fact raising their faction appropriately to do such a quest, any SK, no matter what race they are, should admire such dedication just to wanting/obtaining such a relic.  There are many quests that make absolutely no sense in terms of RP in this game, but it comes to a point VI had to look at it in terms of .. are we making this game fun .. or are we making it *too* real.  Imagine if no evil wizard could obtain their epic because one of their pieces needed in fact drops off a mob which in fact is DE Alignment(Venril Sathir).  Or how many folks would create Iksar Shadowknights, if none of them could gain their epic? Quest pieces for Darkforge come off of disciples of Cazic Thule, that doesn't sound too kosher to me.  Some of you will probably come back saying that is in no relation to being able to gain an Iksar Relic, and hell I may even be just a dense Ogre, however I for one feel to gain such an item, you should have to raise your faction to get it, not destroy it.<br>
<br>
However, on a different subject.. Anyone that can obtain the item Ooiioo has asked for, I'll be willing to pay 2kpp for it.. just send me a tell in game.<br>
<br>
<br>
