<br>
Many of those other things, you can come up with personal excuses for without too much trouble. (Because they don't involve an entire player populated society/culture, they tend to just involve your character and non PC races) This, in order for the Iksar to RP it, actually requires you to change how Iksar society is structured and kind of rewrite your character unless the soft skin doing the quest is willing to RP some very specific things. (Basically pretend they swore total loyalty to the Empire and Cazic-Thule above ALL else) <br>
<br>
Iksar just don't tolerate in their city those who aren't completely loyal to their Empire and Cazic-Thule. They don't tolerate those who are selfish, are greedy, don't follow orders, and they don't like or trust outsiders for good reason. Their society is structurd in such a way that they want to be able to have complete faith and trust in every individual they see, soft skins cannot be trusted in that manner and wouldn't be welcome. <br>
<br>
I know there's a point where things become not fun from being too realistic, but this change is, as I said, pretty much UnRPable from the Iksar side with any sense of believability. This isn't just unrealistic, this is taking any sense of realism and throwing it out the window. Since I knew soft skins would come eventually I spent a long time trying to think of an excuse to use about these quests, and I just could not find any that is remotely belivable or doesn't contradict the way Iksar are. If anyone has suggestions on how to RP it, I certainly wouldn't object to hearing them, but I will argue their points if their not sufficent in my eyes, and if they are, all the better.<br>
<br>
It's not just me, either...pretty much every Iksar I've seen with an ounce of roleplaying in them hates this change and thinks it makes no sense RP wise. Even those who are indifferent too it, think it makes no sense RP wise. (Even a good chunck of soft skins think it makes no sense) I mean, maybe if it was Cazicite only...<br>
<br>
I can't blame people for doing the quest, though. It's a nice item. I can even understand the decision to open it to other races if you don't consider the story at all. But I am still mad at Verant for opening it to soft skins. *sighs*  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A> at: 6/25/02 1:17:31 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=2174.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=2174.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2174.topic&index=17><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.threadControl?topicID=2174.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2174.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2174.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="firionaviefrm1">Firiona Vie General Chat<option value="firionaviefrm9">OT/OOC Forum<option value="firionaviefrm4">The Soapbox<option v